Introduction
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
RGG aka Reactor Geometry Generator program is a tool to generate assembly geometry in OpenCascase or ACIS format using CGM (ITAPS, ANL).
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

In order to use rgg program use standard autotools commands:
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
autoreconf -fi;
./configure --with-igeom=<igeom-dir> --with-imesh=<imesh-dir> --with-irel=<irel-dir> --enable-algs --enable-rgg --enable-debug
make
cd rgg; 
make nrgen_test; 
nrgen_test;
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Launch the executable 'nrgen_test' from the rgg directory as follows
usage: nrgen_test <inpufile name WITHOUT EXTENSION> 
RGG by default assumes that:
input file name is  <inpufile name WITHOUT EXTENSION>.inp
geometry file name is  <inpufile name WITHOUT EXTENSION>.sat or brep based on the geometry engine
Journal file name is  <inpufile name WITHOUT EXTENSION>.jou
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

EXAMPLE (Sample input files can be found in files directory in rgg)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
nrgen_test ./files/v1
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Note: .sat is created when compiled with CGM based on ACIS, use .brep when compiled with CGM based on OCC

v1.inp has the following lines:
! #############################################################################################################
! Hexagonal VHTR Control Fuel Block Assembly Definition without CellMaterials (Prism) around individual Pins
! #############################################################################################################
!
GeometryType Hexagonal  
!                                     
Materials 10 Mat_C2Coolant C02 Mat_C1Coolant C01 Mat_OCoolant C1Out Mat_Coolant C1 Mat_SCoolant SC1 Mat_Fuel  F1 Mat_Block G1 Mat_Poison P1 Mat_Control R1 Mat_FHH H1       
!
Dimensions 2 0.0 0.0 -0 793.0 36.0 37.3  G1 C1Out ! 2 outer squares at 0.0 0.0 height 0.0 to 124.0 x1 y1 x2 y2 material1 material2 
!
Pincells 8 1.87960 
! 1
Cell_Fuel       FC 1
Cylinder  1 0.0 0.0    0.0 793.0   0.6225  F1 
! 2
Cell_BurnPoison BP 1
Cylinder  1 0.0 0.0    0.0 793.0   0.6225  P1 
! 3
Cell_SmallCoolant    SC 1
Cylinder  1 0.0 0.0    0.0 793.0   0.6350 SC1
! 4
Cell_Coolant    CC 1
Cylinder  1 0.0 0.0    0.0 793.0   0.79375 C1
! 5
Cell_FuelHandle FH 0
! 6
Cell_Graphite   GC 0
! 7
AVol_Control CR 1                                         
Cylinder  3  0.0 0.0 0.0 793.0 2.64 4.13 4.7625 C01 R1 C02
! 8
AVol_FHH     FH2 1
Cylinder  1  0.0 0.0 0.0 793.0 2.0 H1                     
Assembly 11                                                 
